<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="58" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,310,400,426]" box="[189,310,400,426]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,400,426]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,400,426]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,1401,447,579]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">
The salient features of the new species include: anal segment very short and wide, wider than long (
<figureCitation box="[198,294,482,509]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[252,1341,269,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-103@14.[232,1356,259,1833]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 7. Andes latanalus Wang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862189" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862189/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Fig. 7H</figureCitation>
); basal right side of ventral margin of periandrium with a triangular laminal process, which turns upward to form a long spinose process that bends inward twice at a right angle (
<figureCitation box="[1230,1316,518,544]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[252,1341,269,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-103@14.[232,1356,259,1833]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 7. Andes latanalus Wang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862189" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862189/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Fig. 7J</figureCitation>
); basal ventral margin of endosoma with a small process that bends inward at an acute angle (
<figureCitation box="[1202,1328,553,579]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[252,1341,269,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-103@14.[232,1356,259,1833]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 7. Andes latanalus Wang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862189" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862189/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Fig. 7J–M</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="58" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,324,618,644]" box="[189,324,618,644]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,618,644]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,618,644]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[188,1399,665,727]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">
The specific name is derived frOm the Latin adjective ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wang &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2022" box="[826,935,665,691]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Andes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latanalus">
<emphasis box="[826,935,665,691]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">latanalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, referring to the anal segment which is very wide compared to its length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
