<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="60" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,334,1048,1074]" box="[189,334,1048,1074]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,334,1048,1074]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,1048,1074]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,1219,1095,1122]" box="[189,1219,1095,1122]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">
MEASUREMENTS. Body length: male 
<quantity box="[611,752,1095,1122]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.55" metricValueMax="7.2" metricValueMin="5.9" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" unit="mm" value="6.55" valueMax="7.2" valueMin="5.9">5.9–7.2 mm</quantity>
(N = 19), female 
<quantity box="[962,1104,1095,1122]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.699999999999999" metricValueMax="8.2" metricValueMin="7.2" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" unit="mm" value="7.699999999999999" valueMax="8.2" valueMin="7.2">7.2–8.2 mm</quantity>
(N = 25).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,1401,1160,1398]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">
COLORATION. General color blackish brown (
<figureCitation box="[727,859,1160,1187]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[252,1341,269,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-103@14.[232,1356,259,1833]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 7. Andes latanalus Wang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862189" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862189/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Fig. 7A–B</figureCitation>
). Eyes blackish brown, ocelli reddish brown, semi-translucent. Antenna yellowish brown. Vertex and rostrum generally brown. Face blackish brown. Pronotum yellowish brown. Mesonotum blackish brown. Forewing semi-translucent, basal and middle part with two oblique yellowish brown stripes, margin darker, basal costal vein; slightly anterior to stigma, posterior to stigma, radial area near claval fork and near fork MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1071,1098,1320,1334]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">1+2</subScript>
+MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1162,1189,1320,1334]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">3+4</subScript>
with an irregular puce spot, respectively; apical half of wing with brown patches. Veins light yellowish brown. Stigma and tubercles blackish brown. Hind tibiae yellowish brown. Ventral abdomen yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,1399,1437,1646]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">
HEAD AND THORAX. Vertex (
<figureCitation box="[520,647,1437,1463]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[252,1341,269,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-103@14.[232,1356,259,1833]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 7. Andes latanalus Wang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862189" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862189/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Fig. 7A, C</figureCitation>
) 1.6× as long as wide; lateral carinae strongly elevated, median carina absent. Frons (
<figureCitation box="[449,544,1472,1498]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[252,1341,269,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-103@14.[232,1356,259,1833]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 7. Andes latanalus Wang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862189" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862189/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Fig. 7D</figureCitation>
) 3.6× as long as wide. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[969,1100,1472,1499]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[252,1341,269,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-103@14.[232,1356,259,1833]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 7. Andes latanalus Wang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862189" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862189/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Fig. 7A, C</figureCitation>
) 1.3× as long as vertex; posterior margin forming a right angle. Mesonotum 1.2× as long as pronotum and vertex combined. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[321,450,1543,1569]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[252,1341,269,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-103@14.[232,1356,259,1833]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 7. Andes latanalus Wang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862189" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862189/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Fig. 7B, E</figureCitation>
) 2.2× as long as wide, with twelve apical cells and seven subapical cells; RP with 3 branches; MP with 5 branches: MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[693,709,1597,1611]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">11</subScript>
, MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[768,785,1597,1611]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">12</subScript>
, MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[844,853,1597,1611]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">2</subScript>
, MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[911,920,1597,1611]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">3</subScript>
and MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1022,1031,1597,1611]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">4</subScript>
; fork MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1148,1157,1597,1611]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">1</subScript>
+ MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1223,1232,1597,1611]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">2</subScript>
basad of fork MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[231,240,1632,1646]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">3</subScript>
+MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[306,315,1632,1646]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">4</subScript>
. Metatibiotarsal formula 8/8, second segment of hind tarsus with three platellae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,1400,1679,2021]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">
MALE GENITALIA. Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[505,629,1679,1705]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[252,1341,269,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-103@14.[232,1356,259,1833]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 7. Andes latanalus Wang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862189" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862189/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Fig. 7F–G</figureCitation>
) in ventral view symmetrical; in lateral view, lateral lobes arcuate and extended caudally. Medioventral process lanceolar in ventral view. Anal segment (
<figureCitation box="[1208,1330,1714,1740]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[252,1341,269,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-103@14.[232,1356,259,1833]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 7. Andes latanalus Wang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862189" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862189/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Fig. 7F, H</figureCitation>
) very short, dorsal margin almost straight, ventral margin curved, apical margin truncate in lateral view; 1.5× as wide as long in dorsal view; anal style strap-shaped, extending beyond anal segment. Gonostyli (
<figureCitation box="[198,322,1819,1846]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[252,1341,269,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-103@14.[232,1356,259,1833]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 7. Andes latanalus Wang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862189" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862189/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Fig. 7G, I</figureCitation>
) symmetrical ventrally; in inner lateral view, dorsal margin obtusely emarginate, apical part expanded, then gradually narrowed. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[803,927,1855,1881]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[252,1341,269,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-103@14.[232,1356,259,1833]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 7. Andes latanalus Wang &amp; Chen sp. nOv., ♂. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Head and thorax, dorsal view. D. Face, ventral view. E. Forewing. F. Genitalia, lateral view. G. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view. H. Anal segment, dorsal view. I. Gonostyli, lateral view. J. Aedeagus, right side. K. Aedeagus, left side. L. Aedeagus, dorsal view. M. Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: A–D, F–M = 0.5 mm; E = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6862189" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6862189/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Fig. 7J–M</figureCitation>
) with two processes. Basal right side of ventral margin of periandrium with a triangular laminal process, turning upward to form a long spinose process bending inward twice at a right angle directed right-dorsocephalad. Endosoma claviform, long and slightly curved, basal ventral margin with a small process that bends inward at an acute angle, directed left-ventrocephalad.
</paragraph>
