<subSubSection lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="61" pageId="15" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[189,303,1912,1938]" box="[189,303,1912,1938]" pageId="15" pageNumber="60">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1912,1938]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="15" pageNumber="60" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1912,1938]" pageId="15" pageNumber="60">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[189,1399,1958,2020]" lastBlockId="16.[188,1401,265,397]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="61" pageId="15" pageNumber="60">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Mastsumura, 1914)" baseAuthorityName="Mastsumura" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[491,953,1958,1984]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Andes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosanus">
<emphasis box="[491,708,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="60">Andes formosanus</emphasis>
(Mastsumura, 1914)
</taxonomicName>
in appearance, but differs in: (1) anal segment is very short and wide, much wider than long (anal segment longer than wide in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mastsumura" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[1211,1381,1993,2020]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Andes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosanus">
<emphasis box="[1211,1381,1993,2020]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="60">A. formosanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); (2) basal ventral margin of periandrium with a triangular laminal process, which turns upward to form a long spinose process that bends inward at right angles (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mastsumura" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[882,1054,300,327]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Andes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosanus">
<emphasis box="[882,1054,300,327]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="61">A. formosanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without process in the same position); (3) basal ventral margin of endosoma with a small process that bends inward at an acute angle (endosoma without a spinose process in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mastsumura" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[663,833,371,397]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Andes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosanus">
<emphasis box="[663,833,371,397]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="61">A. formosanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
